[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In today\'s video, we\'re going to be checking out possibly the best window AC unit that you can buy, and it\'s this guy right here. It\'s the Midea U-shaped inverter compressor window unit. There\'s several things that set this unit apart from the rest, so with that, let\'s jump'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'right into it. All right, so for starters, the installation of this window unit was very basic. It had a really nice bracket that just had these little pins that you adjust depending on the thickness of your window. You can'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'install this in a really thick window, no problem, and that bracket super easy. Now, these window units are designed to slope slightly away from the home for drainage, and this bracket made that really easy. It also includes a little'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'level, and that part was super basic, as well. Now, another thing I really like about this unit is that it uses a very small sliver of insulating foam to fill that gap that you have at the bottom of the window. Some other units, you'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'require a lot of foam, and they include a ton of foam, but this kit includes a small amount because they know you\'re not going to need much with the design of this system. Now, with that being said, the main thing that I like about this unit that sets it apart from some'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of the saddle design units that I\'ve reviewed in the past is that with a saddle design, you have water that\'s condensing inside here, and it has to then be pumped over that hump into the outside condenser, whereas this unit,'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'being as it\'s a U-shape, it does not have to do that. It can simply drain right here, and there is no extra unit or pump required to pump that water out. So, the less components, the better, the'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'more simple it is, and that\'s going to make it last a lot longer. Now, more importantly, this unit is 35% more efficient than your standard AC unit, and it is 10 times quieter. That\'s'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what this unit is all about. It\'s supposed to be about 35 decibels. So, I\'m really curious to see how quiet this is compared to some other AC units that I\'ve tested, and the reason this can do that is because it has inverter'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'technology. Something that is included in say a mini split system that you can barely hear that compressor running. That same technology is put in this tiny window unit, which is amazing. Now, real'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quick, let\'s talk about price and capacity. So, this is the 8,000 BTU window unit that can condition 350 sq ft. And funny enough, this unit is $350 with free shipping on Prime. So, a great'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
